		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Even Namco has done some copying: Katamari series is just Bubbles (1982) by Williams, redone as a 3D platformer. But again, original characters and original art style keep it from being a violation.</div>
<br />I don't think this is a fair comparison at all.  There is far more that separates the two games than characters and art style.  You might as well claim that EVE Online is a direct copy of Asteroids or Star Fox is a copy of Millipede.
<br />
<br />Extreme technicalities and vague similarities in the most basic form of gameplay aren't worth considering.

		

